<br>Yes, there are saree which are in your budget and can serve as your daily wear and some can be the fanciest of all.<br><br>However, the different variations and diversities that have been a part of the silk sarees for ages and helps to determine the quality of the sarees. <br><br>The task of choosing good quality silk have become quite a challenge. It is needless to say that all the variations that you get in the market of are not of the same standard. Some of them happen to be really good fakes of the original versions.<br><br>So what could be the remedy? So in my latest blog, we shall discuss some simple steps to <a href="/collections/buy-silk-mark-certified-saree" target="_self" style="color: rgb(0, 71, 178); font-weight: bold;">buy good quality silk mark certified sarees.</a></span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-15_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-17_">Step by Step Guide to Buy Silk Mark Certified Sarees</span></h3><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-18_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-20_"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Check for the Silk Mark Certified Tag.&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;Yes, the first and foremost thing that you need to do is look for the government accredited hologram <span style="font-weight: bold;">tag for the s</span><span style="font-weight: 700;">ilk mark certified sarees. </span>In all our sarees at IndyVogue you will find this card / tag other than our normal price tag that comes along with.&nbsp;<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Check for the Sheen of the Fabric.&nbsp;</span>In a good quality silk there will always be a lustre that perks up the look of the material. However, this will not be a shine of the material. In other words, the saree will not be very loud. Instead, there will be a sophisticated sheen, that will be visible when the saree will be placed in light.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Colors of the saree. </span>Always remember, a good quality silk sarees have sophisticated colors. You can get both light and dark colors but the colors will be crass and loud. You can also find a classy mixture of colors. This can be attained with mixing threads of different colors or at the time of weaving the saree.</span></p><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1469/7362/t/54/assets/237_3_1800x1800-1644431069911.jpeg?v=1644431072" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1469/7362/t/54/assets/237_3_1800x1800-1644431069911.jpeg?v=1644431072 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1469/7362/t/54/assets/237_3_1800x1800-1644431069911_500x.jpeg?v=1644431072 320w" width="640" height="853" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-jQrDum igoalK pf-21_"/><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-22_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-24_">Showing an ikat silk from our inventory with silk mark tags</span></p><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-25_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-27_"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Look for the weight&nbsp;of the saree. </span>Often you will find people debating on this point. Even most of my buyers ask more question on weight&nbsp;more than any other identifier.<span style="font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;</span>It has often been said that a good quality silk saree is more in weight. On the contrary, good quality silk is always light in its weight. Although these sarees have a great fall and the final look of these sarees are really rich and sophisticated.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Touch The Fabric. </span>This is one of the acid tests when you get down to buy a good quality silk mark saree. High quality silk always has a very soft and uniform smoothness to its finish. The feel of the silk will be soft against the skin. There will not be an iota of coarseness to the material. In case you feel any bubble or tufts of thread in a place then avoid the piece. But when you buy online this is not possible to